<item>
            <title>[CXF-8201] Path not appended when using UriBuilder.fromUri().path() with file scheme</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-8201</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/cxf-dev/202001.mbox/%3CCAGRgoZhuKXoYW_JtxyDH%3Du7Qqqcbeo6-9BXa0dxB8L%2BiGB4J4g%40mail.gmail.com%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/cxf-dev/202001.mbox/%3CCAGRgoZhuKXoYW_JtxyDH%3Du7Qqqcbeo6-9BXa0dxB8L%2BiGB4J4g%40mail.gmail.com%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When calling UriBuilder.fromUri(&quot;file:///~/calendar&quot;).path(&quot;extra&quot;).build().toString() - the result is&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;file:///~/calendar&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;file:///~/calendar&lt;/a&gt;, without the &quot;/extra&quot; on the end. CXF 3.1 behaves differently (the /extra is appended).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve requested clarification on the spec:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.eclipse.org/lists/jaxrs-dev/msg00773.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.eclipse.org/lists/jaxrs-dev/msg00773.html&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
